==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orpheus
<hw>Or"phe*us</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>prop. n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Orpheus</ets>, Gr. <?/.]</ety> <fld>(Gr. Myth.)</fld> <def>The
famous mythic Thracian poet, son of the Muse <persfn>Calliope</persfn>,
and husband of <persfn>Eurydice</persfn>. He is reputed to have had
power to entrance beasts and inanimate objects by the music of his
lyre.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orphic</ent>⟦br⟧
